<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
i3ullseye posts:<P>&lt;But i have now been assured this will equal out.&gt;<P>Umm given the previous "assurances" they gave you what makes you think these "assurances" are any more reliable.  I've been playing this game since almost day one of retail, and other than bladeturn and finally, after 6 months, fixing the runspeed issue, I can't think of a single patch that improved our class (well the crit shot did, but not much of a difference for a mind spec sorc I guess, and they'll nerf that with the damage reduction).  Patches, I thought, were supposed to improve the game.  I really rather they'd stop patching entirely, as all they do is violate my expectations and devalue all the work that's gone into my sorc.  I don't know about you, but I've come to dread patch day.  I think Mythic has made its position on sorcs abundantly clear.  I have no expectations anymore that this class will be improved.  Minstrels are now the CC/pet class.  They have mez, confuse, better pets, stealth, armor, weapon, faster speed, and mana regen.  The only place their cc is not adequate for PvE is gobbie camps (they do just fine on trees).  AND if the ae limit of 16 goes into effect, sorcs will be no better on gobbies either.  Minstrels can join an XP group and go afk for hours just for their manasong.  The instacasts alone make them superior in RVR, not even taking into account all their other qualities, such as stealth and speed.  Sure we have longer duration on mezzes, but it's VERY rare that any of my mezzes last anywhere NEAR the full duration in rvr, so that's not much of a selling point.  Their armor permits them to sic an orange pet on an opponent and maybe even survive long enough for the pet to do some good!<P>Has anyone made a list of all the patches and how they've affected sorcerers as opposed to effects on other classes?  I'd sure be curious to see it all in one place.  <P>Anyway, for newer sorcs, I'd suggest rerolling while you still can and taking minstrel if you want sorc-like capabilites.  <P>Tequitus, level 50<BR>Lancelot, 44 mind, 8 matter 30 body.<P><BR>P.S.<BR>i3ullseye, You are not the only TL who has been lied to btw, I seem to recall the theurgist TL almost quitting over some information regarding siege spells.  I think they took the siege spell stuff out of the guide after telling the TL there WOULD be siege spells for theurgs. He had a fit.  Then Mythic backpedaled and said that just because the siege stuff came out of the guide doesn't mean that theurgs will NEVER get siege spells.  ROFL  Ya right!
</FONT>
